# scripts/deploy/

Production deployment scripts and checklists for Opita Market.

## Files

- `production-checklist.sh` — pre-deploy gate. Runs the RNBD prereqs
  sub-check + records the DPO sign-off. **All 10 steps must show OK +
  DPO initials + sign-off date before `sst deploy --stage prod` runs.**

## Workflow

```
# 1. Run the checklist (mandatory gate).
bash scripts/deploy/production-checklist.sh

# 2. If the checklist exits 0, deploy.
npx sst deploy --stage prod

# 3. Run the post-deploy smoke test.
cd apps/market-web
PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL=https://market.opitacode.com npm run test:e2e
```

## Hard rules

- The DPO sign-off gate cannot be bypassed. If the operator does not
  have DPO initials to provide, the deploy is BLOCKED. This is
  intentional: a Habeas Data database going live without DPO sign-off
  violates Ley 1581/2012 Art. 18.
- A failed sub-check (e.g. RNBD prereqs found a missing secret) blocks
  the deploy even if DPO initials are provided.
- The checklist does NOT call `sst deploy` itself — the operator runs
  it after the checklist passes. This keeps the script idempotent and
  auditable.